Sally Beauty Holdings, Inc. (Na (NYSE:SBH) Sees Significantly Lower Trading Volume - Highlight Press

























































Highlight PressBreaking Tech News, Entertainment, Mortgages and More
Sally Beauty Holdings, Inc. (Na (NYSE:SBH) Sees Significantly Lower Trading Volume
July 25, 2017 By Clarence Martin Tweet        Advertisement





Sally Beauty Holdings, Inc. (Na shares had a trading volume of 43K on Tuesday.  Overall, volume was down 95.67% under the stocks normal daily volume. 
 Sally Beauty Holdings, Inc. (Na (NYSE:SBH) has been the object of insider buying activity recently.   John A. Miller, Director reported the purchase of 20,000 shares of SBH stock. The shares were bought on June 2nd for an average price of $18.35. Miller now owns $730,367 of the stock according to the SEC filing. Director Edward W. Rabin disclosed the purchase of 3,500 shares. The shares sold for $17.67. The Director now owns $272,171 of the stock per the Form 4 SEC filing.
 Christian A. Brickman, President & CEO disclosed the purchase of 10,000 shares of (SBH). The shares were purchased at an average price of $17.91. The President & CEO now owns $2,732,045 of the stock per the Form 4 SEC filing.
 These funds have also shifted positions in (SBH).   As of the end of the quarter Empire Life Investments Inc. had bought  a total of 1,151 shares growing its stake by 7.3%. The value of the total investment in Sally Beauty Holdings, Inc. (Na went from $403,000 to $438,000 increasing 8.7% for the reporting period. As of quarter end Proficio Capital Partners LLC had acquired 711 shares growing its position 467.8%. The value of the investment in Sally Beauty Holdings, Inc. (Na increased from $4,000 to $15,000 a change of 275.0% quarter over quarter.
 As of quarter end Tower Research Capital LLC (trc) had sold 2,199 shares trimming its holdings by 93.1%. The value in dollars decreased from $62,000 to $3,000 a change of $59,000 quarter to quarter. Schroder Investment Management Group bolstered its investment by buying 1,160,507 shares an increase of 393.9%. Schroder Investment Management Group now holds 1,455,115 shares with a value of $29,612,000. The total value of its holdings increased 280.4%.
  On July 7, 2017 DA Davidson added the stock to its research portfolio with a rating of “Neutral”. Equity analyst Jefferies initiated coverage setting a rating of “Hold”.





 On September 30 Piper Jaffray held the company rating at “Neutral” and moved down the price target from $31.00 to $27.00. On June 2 the stock rating was upgraded from “Overweight” to “Market Perform” in a statement from Wells Fargo.
 BB&amp;T Capital initiated coverage on SBH giving it an initial rating of “Hold”. March 14 investment analysts at Morgan Stanley held the stock rating at “Equal-weight” and raised the price target  to $32.00 from $30.00.
 The company is now up from yesterday’s close of $19.28.  Company shares last traded at $19.87 which is just over $19.42, the 50 day moving average and a tad below the 200 day moving average of $20.80.  The 50 day moving average went up $0.41 or +2.10% and the 200 day average moved down $-0.97. 
 The most current P/E ratio is 12.30 and the market value is 2.75B.  In the last earnings report the EPS was $1.61 and is estimated to be $1.76 for the current year with 138,593,000 shares outstanding.  Analysts expect next quarter’s EPS to be $0.45 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $1.90. 
 Sally Beauty Holdings, Inc., launched on June 16, 2006, is an international specialty retailer and distributor of professional beauty supplies with operations primarily in North America, South America and Europe. The Company operates through two business segments: Sally Beauty Supply and Beauty Systems Group (BSG). Sally Beauty Supply is a domestic and international chain of cash and carry retail stores, which offers professional beauty supplies to both salon professionals and retail customers primarily in North America, Puerto Rico, and parts of Europe and South America. BSG, including its franchise-based business Armstrong McCall, is a full service beauty supply distributor, which offers professional brands of beauty products directly to salons and salon professionals through its own sales force and professional-only stores (including franchise stores) in partially exclusive geographical territories in North America and parts of Europe. As of September 30, 2016, the Company operated a multi-channel platform of 4,937 company-operated stores and supplied 182 franchised stores. Sally Beauty Supply targets retail consumers and salon professionals, while BSG targets salons and salon professionals..






