Home/Our Company/History Timeline





        History Timeline
      

MENU

History TimelineCompany ProfileGlobal LocationsLeadership
Board of DirectorsManagement











 1964  1978  1982  1999  2000  Present  

















 1964








 






1964
First Sally store opens in New Orleans.





Sally Beauty Supply began operations as a single store in New
                                                Orleans in 1964.












 1969








 






1969
Alberto-Culver acquires Sally Beauty.





In 1969, consumer products company, Alberto-Culver, purchased
                                                what has grown to become an 11-store operation at Sally Beauty.












 1972








 






1972
Michael Renzulli appointed to run Sally Beauty operations





Mike Renzulli, a former Philadelphia pharmacist, is employed at
                                                Alberto-Culver as a brand manager. Leonard Lavin asks Renzulli to
                                                move to New Orleans to head up Sally Beauty, a small cash-and-carry
                                                beauty supply store.












 1978








 






1978
Sally Beauty Supply reaches 25 stores





During the 1970's, Sally Beauty began an aggressive rollout of
                                                stores and by 1978 had a total of 25 stores.












 1982








 






1982
Sally Beauty headquarters moves to Denton, Texas





Sally headquarters moves to Denton, Texas. Between organic
                                                growth and acquisitions, store count reaches 119.












 1985








 






1985
Sally acquires 39 professional-only beauty supply stores





Sally Beauty Company acquires 39 Victory Beauty Systems stores,
                                                a professional-only distributor, which would later become Beauty
                                                Systems Group (BSG).












 1987








 






1987
Sally Beauty enters Europe and celebrates 500th store opening





Sally Beauty Supply enters its first International venture
                                                through the acquisition of 30 Ogee beauty stores based in the U.K.
                                                At home, Sally celebrates the opening of its 500th store and more
                                                than $130 million in sales and moves into its new Support Center at
                                                3900 Morse Street in Denton.












 1991








 






1991
Sally Beauty opens its 1,000th store





Through aggressive growth and acquisitions, Sally Beauty Supply
                                                reaches its 1,000th store opening.












 1993








 






1993
Sally extends operations to Puerto Rico





Sally Beauty Company reaches $500 million in sales and expands
                                                operations to Puerto Rico.












 1994








 






1994
Sally reaches 1,200th store mark 





Sally Beauty Supply reaches 1,200 stores and launches
                                                "CelebHead", a national survey on best star hairstyles and consumer
                                                beauty trends. Sally Beauty Company acquires Bailey's Professional
                                                Beauty, adding sixteen stores to Beauty Systems Group and five
                                                stores to Sally Beauty Supply.












 1996








 






1996
Sally Beauty expands into Germany and celebrates the 1,500th store mark





R.M. Barnum Beauty Supply and F.H. Loeffler are acquired and
                                                combined with Victory Beauty Supply to create Beauty Systems Group
                                                (BSG). Sally Beauty Supply expands its International footprint into
                                                Germany and celebrates the 1,500th store mark. Sally
                                                Beauty Company launches SallyCares, a philanthropic program to
                                                support breast cancer research, Cosmetology Advancement Foundation
                                                (CAF) scholarship fund and the Shelter Program, a program to help
                                                victims of domestic abuse.












 1998








 






1998
Beauty Systems Group enters Canada via acquisition





Beauty Systems Group enters Canada via the acquisitions of
                                                Beauticians' and Jaguar. Net sales for Sally Beauty Supply reaches
                                                the $1 billion mark with 1,800 Sally stores.












 1999








 
Magna aliqua ut enim ad minim veniam





1999
Beauty Systems Group acquires Heil Beauty Supply





Beauty Systems Group acquires Heil Beauty Supply, a full-service
                                                distributor with 34 professional-only stores.












 2000








 






2000
Beauty Systems Group acquires Davidson Beauty Supply





Beauty Systems Group acquires Davidson Beauty Supply, a
                                                full-service distributor with 32 professional-only stores.












 2001








 






2001
Sally Beauty Supply enters Mexico and BSG acquires Armstrong McCall





Sally Beauty Supply enters Mexico through a small acquisition.
                                                Sally's e-commerce website debuts featuring information and
                                                education for Sally's retail and professional customers. Sally
                                                Beauty stores number 2,300 and Beauty Systems Group purchases 130
                                                Armstrong McCall franchised stores.












 2003








 






2003
Beauty Systems Group acquires West Coast Beauty Supply





Sally Beauty Company breaks ground for a new 200,000-sq-ft
                                                Worldwide Support Center in Denton, Texas. Beauty Systems Group
                                                expands into the Western U.S. with the acquisition of West Coast
                                                Beauty Supply, a full-service distributor of professional beauty
                                                products with 123 stores.












 2004








 






2004
Sally Beauty Supply enters Canada and reaches 2,400 stores worldwide





Sally Beauty Supply expands its presence to Canada. Sally
                                                continues its ongoing support of breast cancer research at City of
                                                Hope and presented a check for $100,000 at the annual gala event in
                                                Las Vegas bringing the total that Sally Beauty has raised to more
                                                than $3 million. Halle Berry wins Best Female Celebrity Hair in the
                                                Sally "CelebHead" consumer poll for the third year in a row. Sally
                                                Beauty reaches 2,400 stores and $1.4 billion in sales.












 2005








 






2005
Sally Beauty Holdings moves into its new Denton, Texas headquarters.





Also in 2005, Beauty Systems Group entered the Los Angeles and Hawaiian marketplace to expand into the Western U.S. through the acquisition of 93 CosmoProf stores.












 2006








 






2006
Sally Beauty Holdings [NYSE:SBH] becomes an independent public Company





In June 2006, Beauty Systems Group (BSG) acquired U.K. based
                                                Salon Success (www.salon-success.co.uk ). Salon Success is the sole U.K. distributor of Paul
                                                Mitchell Luxury Hair Care products.　 On November 16, 2006 Sally
                                                Beauty Holdings becomes an independent public company and Gary
                                                Winterhalter is named President and CEO.












 2007








 






2007
Sally Beauty acquires UK based Salon Services 





In February 2007, Sally Beauty Holdings acquired Salon Services
                                                based in the UK providing a strong European presence for the
                                                Company. At the time of the acquisition, Salon Services had
                                                approximately 100 stores located in U.K, Ireland, Germany and
                                                Spain.












 2008








 






2008
Sally Beauty acquires Belgium based Pro-Duo





In May 2008, Sally Beauty Holdings acquired Pro-Duo, a European
                                                distributor of professional beauty products. Pro-Duo is based in
                                                Belgium and as of the acquisition date, operated 40 stores in
                                                Belgium, France, and Spain. This acquisition provided the Sally
                                                Beauty Supply business an important geographic foothold throughout
                                                key areas of Continental Europe.
www.pro-duo.com












 2009








 






2009
Sally Beauty Supply made its entre into South America through the acquisition of Chile-based InterSalon, based in Santiago, Chile. Today, the stores are branded Sally.





Also in 2009, Beauty Systems Group (BSG) acquired Schoeneman Beauty Supply, Inc., a leading full-service distributor of professional beauty products.  At the time of the acquisition, the Company owned 43 professional-only beauty supply stores located in Pennsylvania, Southern New Jersey, Northern Delaware and West Virginia.












 2010








 






2010
Sally reaches its 4,000th stores and BSG acquires Aerial





Sally Beauty Holdings opened its 4,000th store in Charlotte,
                                                North Carolina on July 19, 2010. The Company is now located in 11
                                                countries around the world with annual revenue of $2.6 billion. In
                                                October 2010, Beauty Systems Group acquired Aerial Company, Inc., a
                                                leading distributor in the professional beauty products industry
                                                with 82 stores and 70 direct sales consultants in the Midwest
                                                region of the U.S.












 2011








 






2011
Sally Beauty acquires Netherland based Floral Group





In November 2011, Sally Beauty Holdings, Inc. acquired
                                                Netherland based Kappersservice Floral B.V. and two related
                                                companies, Hair Zone B.V. and Exphair B.V. (the "Floral Group").
                                                The Floral Group is headquartered in Eindhoven, Netherlands and
                                                operates three concepts in the beauty industry that serve the
                                                professional and retail consumer.












 2012








 






2012
Belgium based Pro-Duo celebrates its 10th anniversary





Belgium based Pro-Duo celebrates its 10th anniversary. Pro-Duo
                                                is Europe's largest wholesale distributor of professional hair and
                                                beauty products with shops and catalogue sales in France, Belgium,
                                                Germany and Spain.
www.pro-duo.com












 2013








 






2013
Sally U.K. opens its flagship store





Sally U.K. opens its three-story flagship store on Oxford Street
                                                in London












 2014








 






2014
Sally Beauty opens its first store in Peru.





Sally Beauty Supply expanded its presence to Peru on January 28,
                                                2014.












 2016








 






2016
Sally Beauty opens its first store in Colombia.















 2016








 






2016
Sally Beauty Holdings opened their 5,000th store location in Fort Worth, TX


































